author: kaushalye
msg: Introducing new strict security header processor for Rampart/C.
This would be more strict on the order of elements in the security header.
The approach is taken in order to enhance the interoprability between Rampart/C and other WS-Security implementations.
This is the common approach for Rampart/Java as well.

author: jliu
msg: Did some format stuff to make README files look more consistent. Avoid using hard-coded sample directory names such as "From the samples/jaxws_async directory run the commands", instead using a relative path to refer to the directory name, such as "From the base directory of this sample (i.e., where this README file is located)".
